He was the son of Karl Julius Killingberg and Maren Anette Dahl [strindahistorielag](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). He married Gunda Grendahl in 1932 and had two children: Per Killingberg and Ludvig Georg Killingberg [strindahistorielag](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

He was the son of Ludvig Georg Killingberg (1896-1963) and Gunda Grendahl [strindahistorielag](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). He married Eva Nyberg in 1960 and had five children: Ludvig Georg, Gunnar Atle, Petter, Jørgen, and Gunn Eva [strindahistorielag](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). He owned Tomset farm in Strinda [strindahistorielag](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). Professionally, he worked as an assistant physician and district doctor in various locations in Norway [strindahistorielag](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).

Ludvig Killingberg's research at NTNU focuses on Bayesian deep learning and reinforcement learning [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0). He started his Ph.D. in October 2019, with Helge Langseth as his main supervisor [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).

Specific techniques and algorithms employed in his research include:

*   **Bayesian Exploration in Deep Reinforcement Learning:** Killingberg and Langseth published a paper on this topic in 2023 [cristin](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3). The key idea involves using a Bayesian deep network to represent the posterior distribution over Q(s,a) given the history, and then using Thompson sampling to balance exploration and exploitation efficiently [ceur-ws](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4). The research uses function-space variational inference to encode prior knowledge, modeling the posterior process over the model's output rather than the posterior distribution over the parameters [ceur-ws](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4). This approach relates to Q-learning, but the core idea can also be applied to policy-based methods [ceur-ws](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   **Moment-Matching Distributional Reinforcement Learning:** Killingberg and Langseth also published a paper in 2023 on using the multiquadric kernel for this purpose [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [cristin](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2).
*   **Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for Flexible Variational Posteriors in Bayesian Neural Networks:** In his master's thesis, Killingberg developed a novel method for Bayesian inference in neural networks using GANs [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6). He demonstrated that neural networks could approximate the KL-divergence between two distributions and used this with a generative network to learn the posterior distribution of weights in a Bayesian neural network [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5). The results showed that this method could compete with state-of-the-art methods in terms of accuracy and predictive uncertainty [ntnu](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **Linearised Laplace approximation:** Killingberg leverages the linearised Laplace approximation to equip pre-trained neural networks with the uncertainty estimates provided by their tangent linear models [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). This turns the problem of Bayesian inference in neural networks into one of Bayesian inference in conjugate Gaussian-linear models [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).

It aims to provide tools for learning and implementing various reinforcement learning algorithms, including tabular, deep, offline, multi-agent, and model-based reinforcement learning [juliareinforcementlearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). The package is open source, MIT licensed, and relies on contributions from various individuals [juliareinforcementlearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2).

*   **Reusability and Extensibility:** Offers components and interfaces to help users implement new algorithms [juliareinforcementlearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2) [juliareinforcementlearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
*   **Feature-rich Environments:** Provides built-in environments and third-party wrappers for evaluating algorithms in different scenarios [juliapackages](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4) [juliareinforcementlearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0) [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2).
